This paper is about keyphrase generation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically focuses on the abstractive approach based on neural networks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, the paper also discusses various aspects of extractive keyphrase generation methods, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions trends and patterns in keyphrase generation and text summarization research, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
